To initialize local git repository
$ git init

To check remote origin name
$ git remote -v

> origin git@github.com:Chetansoni123/MicroservicesProject.git (fetch)
> origin git@github.com:Chetansoni123/MicroservicesProject.git (push)

List all the branches in your local repositories
$ git branch -a

Fetch all the remote branches into your local repositories
$ git fetch origin

Rename the existing master to main branch
$ git branch -m master main

To tranfer current files/folders to main branch of my remote repository
$ git checkout main

Pull the latest changes from the remote main to avoid conflicts
$ git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories

Update the remote repository with the new branch name
$ git push origin main
